=== Series three (2013) ===
On 9 July 2012, May announced on his Facebook page that filming had started on the third series.<ref>{{cite web|title=James May update|url=http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=401574036565984&set=a.398173263572728.14947073.372864149436973&type=1&relevant_count=1|archive-url=https://archive.is/20121129063218/http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=401574036565984&set=a.398173263572728.14947073.372864149436973&type=1&relevant_count=1|dead-url=yes|archive-date=29 November 2012|publisher=[[Facebook]]|date=9 July 2012}} </ref> In January 2013, May announced via his Twitter that Man Lab was due to air in March, after the next series of ''[[Top Gear (2002 TV series)|Top Gear]]'' had finished.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=MrJamesMay|author=James May|number=288368433291214848|date=7 January 2013|title=News: Manlab will be shown when the next series of TG has ended. So that could mean March. #CouldAlsoMean2020}}</ref> The series began at 8pm on 28 March 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/episode/vwzgc/james-mays-man-lab--series-3---episode-1|title=James May's Man Lab|publisher=''[[Radio Times]]''|last=Butcher|first=Dave|accessdate=18 March 2013}}</ref>

